The paper deals with transferring Deep Reinforcement Learning policies learned in simulated environments to the real-world domain for visual control tasks. This involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques, as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) methods. The paper also discusses the efficiency and flexibility of the proposed solution, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY).
